<paragraph blockId="11.[130,777,1045,2028]" box="[132,393,1045,1072]" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">
DATA FOR 
<taxonomicName authority="Latreille, 1810" box="[247,393,1046,1072]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">ORTHOPTERA</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="236" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[130,777,1045,2028]" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">
One of us (AL) focused on 
<taxonomicName authority="Acridomorpha. The" authorityName="Acridomorpha. The" box="[436,775,1076,1102]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Orthoptera Acridomorpha.The</taxonomicName>
data summarized in Table 4 were used to produce distributional maps by species or groups of species, which proved reasonably accurate to interpret their distributions according to environmental data, or confirmed taxonomic hypotheses. 33 species of Caelifera have been recorded (Table 4). Among these, three Pamphaginae Burmeister, 1840, viz. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bolivar, 1936)" baseAuthorityName="Bolivar" baseAuthorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Paracinipe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exarata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Paracinipe exarata</emphasis>
(Bolivar, 1936)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Morales Agacino, 1945" authorityName="Morales Agacino" authorityYear="1945" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Glauvarovia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mendizabali">
<emphasis box="[404,677,1299,1325]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Glauvarovia mendizabali</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Morales Agacino" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="310 - 339" part="20" publicationUrl="http://hdl.handle.net/10261/148685" refId="ref12923" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. 1945 a. - Algunos datos sobre orthopteroides del Sahara Occidental. Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia 20 (3 - 4): 310 - 339. http: // hdl. handle. net / 10261 / 148685" title="Algunos datos sobre orthopteroides del Sahara Occidental" type="journal article" year="1945">Morales Agacino, 1945</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Morales Agacino &amp; Descamps, 1968" authorityName="Morales Agacino &amp; Descamps" authorityYear="1968" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Glauia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saharae">
<emphasis box="[368,535,1331,1357]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Glauia saharae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Morales Agacino &amp; Descamps" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe entomologique de France (N. S.)" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="419 - 435" part="4" refId="ref13223" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. &amp; DESCAMPS M. 1968. - Contribution a la faune du Maroc. I. Genres Glauia I. Bolivar, Glauvarovia Morales Agacino et Pseudoglauia nov. [Orth. Pamphagidae]. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France (N. S.) 4 (2): 419 - 435." title="Contribution a la faune du Maroc. I. Genres Glauia I. Bolivar, Glauvarovia Morales Agacino et Pseudoglauia nov. [Orth. Pamphagidae]" type="journal article" year="1968">Morales Agacino &amp; Descamps, 1968</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, were found to be the southernmost of the 83 species of Pamphaginae known from North Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Morales Agacino &amp; Descamps" box="[141,524,1427,1454]" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe entomologique de France (N. S.)" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="419 - 435" part="4" refId="ref13223" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. &amp; DESCAMPS M. 1968. - Contribution a la faune du Maroc. I. Genres Glauia I. Bolivar, Glauvarovia Morales Agacino et Pseudoglauia nov. [Orth. Pamphagidae]. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France (N. S.) 4 (2): 419 - 435." title="Contribution a la faune du Maroc. I. Genres Glauia I. Bolivar, Glauvarovia Morales Agacino et Pseudoglauia nov. [Orth. Pamphagidae]" type="journal article" year="1968">Morales Agacino &amp; Descamps 1968</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Descamps" box="[536,709,1427,1454]" firstAuthor="Descamps" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="24 - 36" part="75" refId="ref11288" refString="DESCAMPS M. 1970. - Contribution a la faune du Maroc. III. Acridoidea du Maroc saharien et Dericorythinae [Orth]. Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France 75 (1 - 2): 24 - 36." title="Contribution a la faune du Maroc. III. Acridoidea du Maroc saharien et Dericorythinae [Orth]." type="journal article" year="1970">Descamps 1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Chobanov &amp; Massa" firstAuthor="Chobanov" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="409 - 425" part="5104" refId="ref10989" refString="CHOBANOV D. &amp; MASSA D. 2022. - On some Moroccan Pamphagidae, with the description of Euryparyphes (Orthoptera: Caelifera). Zootaxa 5104 (3): 409 - 425. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 5104.3.3" title="On some Moroccan Pamphagidae, with the description of Euryparyphes (Orthoptera: Caelifera)" type="journal article" year="2022">Chobanov &amp; Massa 2022</bibRefCitation>
). All the four genera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacobson &amp; Biancchi" authorityYear="1905" box="[611,775,1459,1485]" class="Insecta" family="Dericorythidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Dericorythidae</taxonomicName>
known from North Africa are present in the studied area, including one genus represented by a single endemic species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Morales Agacino, 1949" authorityName="Morales Agacino" authorityYear="1949" box="[130,645,1554,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Dericorythidae" genus="Bolivaremia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="domenechi">
<emphasis box="[130,379,1554,1580]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Bolivaremia domenechi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Morales Agacino" box="[386,645,1554,1581]" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="145 - 174" part="25" publicationUrl="http://hdl.handle.net/10261/151226" refId="ref13182" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. 1949. - Mas notas sobre ortopteroides del Sahara Occidental e Ifni. Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia 25: 145 - 174. http: // hdl. handle. net / 10261 / 151226" title="Mas notas sobre ortopteroides del Sahara Occidental e Ifni" type="journal article" year="1949">Morales Agacino, 1949</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. In contrast to the many species originating from the Mediterranean border of Sahara, only three taxa, 
<taxonomicName authority="melanorhodon (Walker, 1829)" authorityName="melanorhodon (Walker" authorityYear="1829" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Anacridium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="melanorhodon" subSpecies="melanorhodon">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Anacridium melanorhodon melanorhodon</emphasis>
(Walker, 1829)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Klug, 1829)" baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgomorphidae" genus="Poekilocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bufonius" subSpecies="hieroglyphicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Poekilocerus bufonius hieroglyphicus</emphasis>
(Klug, 1829)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Saussure, 1884" authorityName="Saussure" authorityYear="1884" class="Insecta" family="Acrididae" genus="Sphingonotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="canariensis">
<emphasis box="[418,672,1682,1708]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Sphingonotus canariensis</emphasis>
Saussure, 1884
</taxonomicName>
, are Sahelian species that extend occasionally to Rio de Oro. 
<bibRefCitation author="Morales Agacino" box="[222,495,1746,1773]" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="310 - 339" part="20" publicationUrl="http://hdl.handle.net/10261/148685" refId="ref12923" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. 1945 a. - Algunos datos sobre orthopteroides del Sahara Occidental. Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia 20 (3 - 4): 310 - 339. http: // hdl. handle. net / 10261 / 148685" title="Algunos datos sobre orthopteroides del Sahara Occidental" type="journal article" year="1945" yearSuffix="a">Morales Agacino (1945a)</bibRefCitation>
collected eight nymphs of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[130,493,1778,1804]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgomorphidae" genus="Poekilocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bufonius" subSpecies="hieroglyphicus">
<emphasis box="[130,493,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Poekilocerus bufonius hieroglyphicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 1 ♂ and 1 ♀ nymphs (15. IV.1943) at Leglat = Derramán and 6 larvae (14.XII.1941) close to Zug. One of us (AG) observed also one larva at Derramán, west of Aousserd (22°36’N, 14°28’W; 360 m, 19-20. XII.2017). Such breeding, in localities where the obligatory host plant, i.e., 
<taxonomicName authority="Aiton, 1811" authorityName="Aiton" authorityYear="1811" box="[300,629,1937,1963]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Apocynaceae" genus="Calotropis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="procera">
<emphasis box="[300,487,1937,1963]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Calotropis procera</emphasis>
Aïton, 1811
</taxonomicName>
, has not been found, is unlikely to result in fertile population (
<bibRefCitation author="Popov &amp; McE Kevan" firstAuthor="Popov" journalOrPublisher="Anti-Locust Bulletin" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="1 - 81" part="51" refId="ref13600" refString="POPOV B. G. &amp; MCE KEVAN D. K. 1979. - A revision of the genus Poekilocerus Audinet-Serville 1831 (Orthoptera: Acridoidae). Anti-Locust Bulletin 51: 1 - 81." title="A revision of the genus Poekilocerus Audinet-Serville 1831 (Orthoptera: Acridoidae)" type="journal article" year="1979">Popov &amp; McE Kevan 1979</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[811,1456,1044,1326]" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">
We detailed below some of the questions that the inventories of Morales Agacino could help reanalysing, namely the synonymy between 
<taxonomicName authority="Morales Agacino, 1949" authorityName="Morales Agacino" authorityYear="1949" box="[987,1455,1108,1134]" class="Insecta" family="Dericorythidae" genus="Pamphagulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mateui">
<emphasis box="[987,1202,1108,1134]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Pamphagulus mateui</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Morales Agacino" box="[1207,1455,1108,1134]" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="145 - 174" part="25" publicationUrl="http://hdl.handle.net/10261/151226" refId="ref13182" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. 1949. - Mas notas sobre ortopteroides del Sahara Occidental e Ifni. Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia 25: 145 - 174. http: // hdl. handle. net / 10261 / 151226" title="Mas notas sobre ortopteroides del Sahara Occidental e Ifni" type="journal article" year="1949">Morales Agacino, 1949</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Ramme, 1931" authorityName="Ramme" authorityYear="1931" box="[857,1225,1140,1167]" class="Insecta" family="Dericorythidae" genus="Pamphagulus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vicinus">
<emphasis box="[857,1070,1140,1166]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Pamphagulus vicinus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ramme" box="[1075,1225,1140,1167]" firstAuthor="Ramme" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum Berlin" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="165 - 200" part="17" refId="ref13685" refString="RAMME W. A. T. 1931. - Beitrage zur Kenntnis der palaearktischen Orthopterenfauna (Tettig. Et Acrid.). Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum Berlin 17: 165 - 200." title="Beitrage zur Kenntnis der palaearktischen Orthopterenfauna (Tettig. Et Acrid.)" type="journal article" year="1931">Ramme, 1931</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacobson &amp; Biancchi" authorityYear="1905" box="[1238,1405,1140,1167]" class="Insecta" family="Dericorythidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Dericorythidae</taxonomicName>
); the type locality of 
<taxonomicName authority="Morales Agacino, 1949" authorityName="Morales Agacino" authorityYear="1949" box="[967,1451,1172,1198]" class="Insecta" family="Dericorythidae" genus="Bolivaremia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="domenechi">
<emphasis box="[967,1202,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Bolivaremia domenechi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Morales Agacino" box="[1207,1451,1172,1198]" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="145 - 174" part="25" publicationUrl="http://hdl.handle.net/10261/151226" refId="ref13182" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. 1949. - Mas notas sobre ortopteroides del Sahara Occidental e Ifni. Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia 25: 145 - 174. http: // hdl. handle. net / 10261 / 151226" title="Mas notas sobre ortopteroides del Sahara Occidental e Ifni" type="journal article" year="1949">Morales Agacino, 1949</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; the location of Aserifa, a paratype locality of 
<taxonomicName authority="Morales Agacino, 1949" authorityName="Morales Agacino" authorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Dericorythidae" genus="Bolivaremia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="domenechi" subSpecies="laevigata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="236">Bolivaremia domenechi laevigata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Morales Agacino" box="[1002,1255,1236,1262]" firstAuthor="Morales Agacino" journalOrPublisher="Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia" pageId="11" pageNumber="236" pagination="145 - 174" part="25" publicationUrl="http://hdl.handle.net/10261/151226" refId="ref13182" refString="MORALES AGACINO E. 1949. - Mas notas sobre ortopteroides del Sahara Occidental e Ifni. Eos: Revista Espanola de Entomologia 25: 145 - 174. http: // hdl. handle. net / 10261 / 151226" title="Mas notas sobre ortopteroides del Sahara Occidental e Ifni" type="journal article" year="1949">Morales Agacino, 1949</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; and the extension of the distributions of pamphagid grasshoppers in the Atlantic Sahara as documented by Morales Agacino collections.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
